headline: Dell stock target cut at BofA on rising memory costs
summary: Investing.com -- Bank of America believes rising memory prices are set to weigh on Dell Technologies’ near-term profitability, prompting the bank to trim its price target to $135 from $150 per share in a note on Monday, while reiterating a Buy rating.
